        <h1>F I T N E S S </h1><br>
        <h3>🏋️‍♂️ What is Fitness?</h3>
        <strong><p>Fitness refers to the state of being physically healthy, strong, and active. It's not just about having a muscular body or losing weight—it’s about overall well-being, including:</p></strong>
        <ul>
            <li>Cardiovascular endurance (how well your heart and lungs work)</li>
            <li>Muscle strength and endurance</li>
            <li>Flexibility</li>
            <li>Body composition (the ratio of fat to muscle)</li>
        </ul><br>
        <h3>🧠 Why is Fitness Important?</h3>
        <ul>
            <li>Boosts energy levels</li>
            <li>Reduces risk of diseases (like heart disease, diabetes, obesity)</li>
            <li>Improves mental health and reduces stress</li>
            <li>Enhances sleep quality</li>
            <li>Builds self-confidence</li>
        </ul><br>
        <h3>Types of Exercises</h3>
       <ul>
        <li>Aerobic (Cardio) – Running, cycling, swimming</li>
        <li>Strength Training – Weight lifting, resistance bands</li>
        <li>Flexibility – Yoga, stretching</li>
        <li>Balance – Tai chi, balance drills</li>
       </ul>
       <p><strong>👉 Experts recommend at least 30 minutes of moderate exercise, 5 days a week.</strong></p>
